1
00:00:01,140 --> 00:00:12,250
♪

2
00:00:12,250 --> 00:00:15,130
(singing in foreign language)

3
00:00:15,130 --> 00:01:33,100
♪

4
00:01:35,240 --> 00:01:37,170
Hold it, princess.

5
00:01:37,170 --> 00:01:39,080
Shura, the leader
of the pirates,

6
00:01:39,080 --> 00:01:43,030
was betrayed by Ginjo,
her second-in-command.

7
00:01:43,030 --> 00:01:44,100
Stay away from me!

8
00:01:44,100 --> 00:01:45,180
Her life was in danger

9
00:01:45,180 --> 00:01:48,220
because her entire crew
had turned against her.

10
00:01:48,220 --> 00:01:50,180
We don't need you anymore.

11
00:01:50,180 --> 00:01:52,060
(groaning)

12
00:01:52,060 --> 00:01:53,060
No!

13
00:01:53,060 --> 00:01:54,090
She would've been killed,

14
00:01:54,090 --> 00:01:56,160
but luckily Kenshin rescued her.

15
00:01:56,160 --> 00:01:58,030
♪

16
00:01:58,030 --> 00:01:59,220
(water rushing)

17
00:01:59,220 --> 00:02:03,050
♪

18
00:02:04,110 --> 00:02:07,270
(water rushing)

19
00:02:14,010 --> 00:02:15,210
Well, fellas,
she's dead now.

20
00:02:15,210 --> 00:02:17,160
There's no way
anyone could have lived

21
00:02:17,160 --> 00:02:19,130
after falling
from way up here.

22
00:02:19,130 --> 00:02:21,060
That's the end of Shura.

23
00:02:21,060 --> 00:02:23,090
No one could've
lived after that.

24
00:02:23,090 --> 00:02:24,200
(laughing)

25
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:27,280
But I won't be satisfied
until I see her dead body.

26
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:29,170
-Go get it.
-You heard him.

27
00:02:29,170 --> 00:02:30,280
Aye, aye!

28
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:34,040
(panting)

29
00:02:34,040 --> 00:02:36,010
(groaning)

30
00:02:37,190 --> 00:02:40,280
(explosion)

31
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:43,080
(screaming)

32
00:02:53,250 --> 00:02:57,020
(panting)

33
00:02:57,020 --> 00:02:59,060
I have to do something
about her wound.

34
00:02:59,060 --> 00:03:01,140
I wish Dr. Gensai
were here to help me.

35
00:03:01,140 --> 00:03:04,220
Huh?

36
00:03:04,220 --> 00:03:05,270
It's you.

37
00:03:05,270 --> 00:03:07,110
Mm-hm.

38
00:03:07,110 --> 00:03:09,150
-Mm.
-Mm.

39
00:03:13,010 --> 00:03:15,260
(grunting)

40
00:03:15,260 --> 00:03:20,080
The bullet is still
lodged inside of her leg.

41
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:23,010
That bullet has to come out,
otherwise she'll lose her leg.

42
00:03:23,010 --> 00:03:24,070
(gasps)

43
00:03:24,070 --> 00:03:26,110
This is your hiding place,
you're sure we'll be safe here?

44
00:03:26,110 --> 00:03:27,060
Mm-hm, mm-hm.

45
00:03:27,060 --> 00:03:28,210
I'll need dry,
clean cloths,

46
00:03:28,210 --> 00:03:30,100
as many as you can
find, all right?

47
00:03:30,100 --> 00:03:31,140
Mm-hm, mm-hm.

48
00:03:31,140 --> 00:03:34,050
And I'll need some
hot water right away.

49
00:03:40,020 --> 00:03:44,190
I'm no doctor, but right now,
we don't have a choice.

50
00:03:44,190 --> 00:03:47,130
I'm sorry.

51
00:03:47,130 --> 00:03:49,160
I just hope I'm doing
the right thing.

52
00:03:49,160 --> 00:03:51,060
Hang in there, Shura.

53
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:56,290
(panting)

54
00:03:56,290 --> 00:03:59,160
Sanosuke!

55
00:03:59,160 --> 00:04:01,090
Kori, I'm glad to
see you made it.

56
00:04:01,090 --> 00:04:03,170
Yeah, well, it'll take
more than a little explosion

57
00:04:03,170 --> 00:04:06,070
to get rid of me; besides,
we have to go find Kenshin.

58
00:04:06,070 --> 00:04:07,200
Wah!

59
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:08,250
Hey, Yoshi!

60
00:04:08,250 --> 00:04:10,250
All right, Yoshi,
I'm glad to see ya!

61
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:12,270
Those guys blew up
the whole ship!

62
00:04:12,270 --> 00:04:15,070
I wouldn't have believed
it if I hadn't seen it.

63
00:04:15,070 --> 00:04:17,210
I'll get even with them
if it's the last thing I do.

64
00:04:17,210 --> 00:04:19,130
Those jerks are gonna pay!

65
00:04:19,130 --> 00:04:21,070
Watch it!

66
00:04:21,070 --> 00:04:22,260
Hey, come on,
you better calm down,

67
00:04:22,260 --> 00:04:24,150
Yoshi, before you
drown yourself.

68
00:04:24,150 --> 00:04:27,210
Save some of that energy for
those nasty pirates, all right?

69
00:04:27,210 --> 00:04:29,150
(fire crackling)

70
00:04:29,150 --> 00:04:40,140
♪

71
00:04:40,140 --> 00:04:42,000
Ooh!

72
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:43,150
Huh?

73
00:04:43,150 --> 00:04:57,290
♪

74
00:04:57,290 --> 00:04:59,270
There, that should
stop the bleeding,

75
00:04:59,270 --> 00:05:01,150
at least for the time being.

76
00:05:01,150 --> 00:05:03,030
The operation went well,

77
00:05:03,030 --> 00:05:04,230
thanks to you, my friend.

78
00:05:04,230 --> 00:05:07,150
Mm-hm, mm-hm.

79
00:05:07,150 --> 00:05:11,110
We should get her out of
these wet clothes right away.

80
00:05:11,110 --> 00:05:13,240
I wish we had a change
of clothes for her.

81
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:15,160
Huh--ah!

82
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:17,050
Mm-hm, mm-hm.

83
00:05:17,050 --> 00:05:19,000
(gasps)

84
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,100
This place is amazing.

85
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:22,060
What a great hideout
you've got here.

86
00:05:22,060 --> 00:05:24,180
♪

87
00:05:24,180 --> 00:05:26,040
Huh?

88
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:28,140
Wow, what a beautiful kimono.

89
00:05:28,140 --> 00:05:30,230
(bird chirping)

90
00:05:35,190 --> 00:05:37,160
(gasps)

91
00:05:37,160 --> 00:05:39,060
Where am I?

92
00:05:43,100 --> 00:05:45,030
(grumbling)

93
00:05:45,030 --> 00:05:46,280
We don't need you anymore.

94
00:05:46,280 --> 00:05:49,080
(groaning)

95
00:05:49,080 --> 00:05:52,130
(sobbing)

96
00:05:57,080 --> 00:05:58,140
(sighs)

97
00:05:58,140 --> 00:06:04,080
♪

98
00:06:04,080 --> 00:06:06,160
(panting)

99
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:10,170
♪

100
00:06:10,170 --> 00:06:11,280
(gasps)

101
00:06:11,280 --> 00:06:13,200
What are you trying
to do with that?

102
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:15,190
Just leave me alone!

103
00:06:15,190 --> 00:06:18,190
Don't rush death.

104
00:06:18,190 --> 00:06:20,050
I'm a failure.

105
00:06:20,050 --> 00:06:23,200
I was even a failure as
the leader of the Sea Dragon.

106
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:26,140
I'd rather kill myself
than face the shame.

107
00:06:26,140 --> 00:06:27,260
I failed.

108
00:06:27,260 --> 00:06:31,020
(sobbing)

109
00:06:31,020 --> 00:06:32,080
Maybe you're right,

110
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:35,040
maybe you're not fit to be
the leader of the Sea Dragon.

111
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:37,240
(gasps)

112
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:39,240
A good leader is
worried about their crew.

113
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:41,290
You still have crewmen
who believe in you.

114
00:06:41,290 --> 00:06:43,150
(gasps)

115
00:06:43,150 --> 00:06:45,250
♪

116
00:06:45,250 --> 00:06:48,030
Sarujiro.

117
00:06:48,030 --> 00:06:49,230
He risked his life to save you.

118
00:06:49,230 --> 00:06:51,070
Would you leave him behind?

119
00:06:51,070 --> 00:06:55,090
Leaders have more
courage than that.

120
00:06:55,090 --> 00:06:56,280
If you want people
to follow you,

121
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:59,110
you're gonna have
to be brave.

122
00:06:59,110 --> 00:07:00,270
Didn't you say
your father wanted

123
00:07:00,270 --> 00:07:02,290
to set an example
for poor children?

124
00:07:02,290 --> 00:07:05,100
The Shura I know would
stand up to any challenge,

125
00:07:05,100 --> 00:07:08,140
no matter how difficult
the situation might be.

126
00:07:08,140 --> 00:07:11,000
That's the kind
of leader you are.

127
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:15,140
♪

128
00:07:15,140 --> 00:07:19,090
Sorry, I didn't mean to
hold your hand so long!

129
00:07:19,090 --> 00:07:20,090
Huh?

130
00:07:20,090 --> 00:07:21,100
You can go now.

131
00:07:21,100 --> 00:07:24,020
I won't try to hurt
myself anymore.

132
00:07:24,020 --> 00:07:26,100
Hmm?

133
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:28,060
-Okay.
-Wait.

134
00:07:28,060 --> 00:07:30,270
Kenshin.

135
00:07:30,270 --> 00:07:32,090
Did you do this?

136
00:07:32,090 --> 00:07:33,210
Mm-hm.

137
00:07:33,210 --> 00:07:35,030
♪

138
00:07:35,030 --> 00:07:37,210
Sarujiro found a change
of clothes for you.

139
00:07:37,210 --> 00:07:39,100
This beautiful kimono.

140
00:07:39,100 --> 00:07:41,270
I think it'll look
very nice on you.

141
00:07:41,270 --> 00:07:44,030
♪

142
00:07:44,030 --> 00:07:45,080
(gasps)

143
00:07:45,080 --> 00:07:48,120
Come on, you've gotta get
out of those wet clothes.

144
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:57,090
♪

145
00:07:58,170 --> 00:08:03,080
♪

146
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:06,200
Listen, Shura,
don't ever forget.

147
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:08,140
The reason that
we became pirates

148
00:08:08,140 --> 00:08:11,060
was to fight our way
out of poverty.

149
00:08:11,060 --> 00:08:13,010
You see, we had to
come up with some way

150
00:08:13,010 --> 00:08:14,290
that we could feed
all of the poor orphans

151
00:08:14,290 --> 00:08:16,220
of our impoverished
fishing village.

152
00:08:16,220 --> 00:08:18,290
But don't forget,
we only attack ships

153
00:08:18,290 --> 00:08:21,120
that belong to evil people.

154
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:22,270
But stealing is still wrong

155
00:08:22,270 --> 00:08:25,120
and a very cowardly way
to go through life.

156
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:27,200
What I really dream about
is to make an honest,

157
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:30,110
productive, decent living.

158
00:08:30,110 --> 00:08:32,130
I'd rather not
steal from anybody,

159
00:08:32,130 --> 00:08:36,160
I merely want to live as a
free, honest man on the sea.

160
00:08:36,160 --> 00:08:38,090
One of these days
when you've gotten older

161
00:08:38,090 --> 00:08:41,020
and are ready to marry someone,
remember what I've said to you.

162
00:08:41,020 --> 00:08:42,070
(gasps)

163
00:08:42,070 --> 00:08:45,200
Why are you acting so
surprised about that, Shura?

164
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:48,170
One day you'll meet a man that
you'll really fall in love with.

165
00:08:48,170 --> 00:08:51,100
Someday you and your husband
will take over my ship.

166
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:53,230
Iwazo.

167
00:08:53,230 --> 00:08:57,060
Yeah, this is your
late mother's kimono,

168
00:08:57,060 --> 00:09:00,220
I found it in my sea chest.

169
00:09:00,220 --> 00:09:03,100
When you get older, Shura,
and you fall in love,

170
00:09:03,100 --> 00:09:06,040
you can wear this kimono
at your wedding.

171
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:08,120
I'll never ever
dress like a girl!

172
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:10,010
(exclamations of disgust)

173
00:09:10,010 --> 00:09:12,250
(laughing)

174
00:09:12,250 --> 00:09:17,010
♪

175
00:09:18,230 --> 00:09:21,170
(waves crashing)

176
00:09:26,150 --> 00:09:27,270
(grunts)

177
00:09:30,030 --> 00:09:31,260
(creaking open)

178
00:09:31,260 --> 00:09:33,220
(gasps)

179
00:09:36,010 --> 00:09:37,290
So, tell me, Geki,
have any of the men

180
00:09:37,290 --> 00:09:39,210
found Shura's body yet?

181
00:09:39,210 --> 00:09:41,130
I have every
available man

182
00:09:41,130 --> 00:09:44,130
searching at the bottom of
the falls right now, Ginjo.

183
00:09:44,130 --> 00:09:47,010
Don't worry, Shura's dead,
but look what I found.

184
00:09:47,010 --> 00:09:48,120
Yeah, what is it?

185
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:49,280
(laughing)

186
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:51,170
Look.

187
00:09:51,170 --> 00:09:54,210
That's Shura's grandfather,
what happened to him?

188
00:09:54,210 --> 00:09:55,180
(laughing)

189
00:09:55,180 --> 00:09:56,180
Oh, nothing much.

190
00:09:56,180 --> 00:09:57,280
We gave him this.

191
00:09:57,280 --> 00:10:00,120
♪

192
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:03,250
You gave him some...opium?

193
00:10:03,250 --> 00:10:06,130
Ooh-wee, that stuff
works like a charm.

194
00:10:06,130 --> 00:10:08,060
So tell me, have you
made any decision

195
00:10:08,060 --> 00:10:09,250
about working with us, Yohi?

196
00:10:09,250 --> 00:10:11,100
Yes, I have, Ginjo.

197
00:10:11,100 --> 00:10:13,120
I've decided that I'm going
to work with you fellows

198
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:15,290
and hopefully we can all
get really wealthy together.

199
00:10:15,290 --> 00:10:16,270
(laughing)

200
00:10:16,270 --> 00:10:18,100
Glad to hear it.

201
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:21,020
Boys, put that old man in
the storeroom, all right?

202
00:10:21,020 --> 00:10:22,160
-All right.
-You got it!

203
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:24,200
♪

204
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:26,220
Ginjo, the party's
ready to start.

205
00:10:26,220 --> 00:10:28,100
From now on,
you're the new boss,

206
00:10:28,100 --> 00:10:30,060
and we only take
orders from you.

207
00:10:30,060 --> 00:10:31,110
Yeah!

208
00:10:31,110 --> 00:10:33,140
Boys, I'm the new
king of the pirates.

209
00:10:33,140 --> 00:10:34,190
(footsteps approaching)

210
00:10:34,190 --> 00:10:35,280
(gasps)

211
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:38,130
(whimpering)

212
00:10:40,020 --> 00:10:41,020
Go on!

213
00:10:41,020 --> 00:10:42,030
(grunting)

214
00:10:42,030 --> 00:10:44,030
Let's go and join
in on the party!

215
00:10:44,030 --> 00:10:46,090
Yeah, I want to drink
till I pass out!

216
00:10:46,090 --> 00:10:47,270
(laughing)

217
00:10:47,270 --> 00:10:49,080
(gasps)

218
00:10:55,140 --> 00:10:57,270
"Someday, Shura,
when you fall in love,

219
00:10:57,270 --> 00:11:00,090
you'll wear your
mother's kimono."

220
00:11:02,050 --> 00:11:04,010
"We found you
a change of clothes.

221
00:11:04,010 --> 00:11:07,020
This will look
very nice on you."

222
00:11:07,020 --> 00:11:08,150
What's going on?

223
00:11:08,150 --> 00:11:09,260
That you, Kenshin?

224
00:11:09,260 --> 00:11:11,010
I was just...

225
00:11:11,010 --> 00:11:12,130
(gasps)

226
00:11:12,130 --> 00:11:15,000
Sarujiro, Iwazo.

227
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:17,080
Shura...Shura, I...

228
00:11:17,080 --> 00:11:19,040
Iwazo!

229
00:11:20,270 --> 00:11:22,120
What happened to you?

230
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:24,020
Tell me, what did
they do to you?

231
00:11:24,020 --> 00:11:27,270
Ginjo got together with Yohi.

232
00:11:27,270 --> 00:11:29,140
That bastard.

233
00:11:29,140 --> 00:11:31,130
They drugged me.

234
00:11:31,130 --> 00:11:32,150
What?

235
00:11:32,150 --> 00:11:35,190
Iwazo, did you say
those creeps drugged you?

236
00:11:35,190 --> 00:11:37,190
Shura, they'll kill you

237
00:11:37,190 --> 00:11:40,230
if they find you here.

238
00:11:40,230 --> 00:11:43,100
That damn Ginjo!

239
00:11:43,100 --> 00:11:44,220
He'll pay.

240
00:11:44,220 --> 00:11:45,888
♪

241
00:11:52,150 --> 00:11:54,280
I have to figure out a way
to get Shura on that boat

242
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:57,220
and get her to
a doctor right away.

243
00:11:57,220 --> 00:11:59,220
-Kenshin!
-Huh?

244
00:12:01,210 --> 00:12:03,000
Shura!

245
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:04,110
Iwazo!

246
00:12:04,110 --> 00:12:06,190
What in the world happened
to you, my old friend?

247
00:12:06,190 --> 00:12:09,000
It seems the pirates
gave him some opium.

248
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:10,230
We have to take him
to the doctor right away.

249
00:12:10,230 --> 00:12:13,070
It could be serious;
let's take that boat down there.

250
00:12:13,070 --> 00:12:15,110
Get going.

251
00:12:15,110 --> 00:12:17,030
Mm-hm.

252
00:12:17,030 --> 00:12:19,230
(groaning)

253
00:12:19,230 --> 00:12:22,060
Iwazo, you'll be okay.

254
00:12:25,130 --> 00:12:27,100
What are you doing?

255
00:12:27,100 --> 00:12:29,060
(grunting)

256
00:12:29,060 --> 00:12:31,080
(crashing)

257
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:35,100
Why did you do that?

258
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:38,180
I'm sorry, but I've got
a score to settle with Ginjo.

259
00:12:38,180 --> 00:12:39,190
(gasps)

260
00:12:39,190 --> 00:12:42,160
Kenshin, make sure they're safe.

261
00:12:42,160 --> 00:12:44,190
This is your
reversed-edge sword.

262
00:12:44,190 --> 00:12:46,070
Here, take it.

263
00:12:46,070 --> 00:12:47,170
(grunting)

264
00:12:49,250 --> 00:12:51,050
Now go on.

265
00:12:51,050 --> 00:12:53,000
Please look after them.

266
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:54,060
Don't go alone!

267
00:12:54,060 --> 00:12:56,090
I can do this!

268
00:12:56,090 --> 00:12:58,030
Huh?

269
00:12:58,030 --> 00:13:01,050
(birds chirping)

270
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:03,060
(panting)

271
00:13:03,060 --> 00:13:05,030
Ah, we finally made it.

272
00:13:05,030 --> 00:13:07,020
I'm really tired.

273
00:13:07,020 --> 00:13:09,040
Now how are we ever
going to find Kenshin?

274
00:13:09,040 --> 00:13:10,260
-Listen up.
-Huh?

275
00:13:10,260 --> 00:13:13,030
Do you hear that
noise down there?

276
00:13:13,030 --> 00:13:16,140
Sounds like some sort of a party
or festival or something.

277
00:13:16,140 --> 00:13:17,170
(drums beating)

278
00:13:17,170 --> 00:13:19,050
It's right near that clearing.

279
00:13:19,050 --> 00:13:20,140
Let's go down there.

280
00:13:20,140 --> 00:13:22,040
Maybe Kenshin's down there.

281
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:23,120
Let's go!

282
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:25,000
(drums beating)

283
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,220
(mumbling)

284
00:13:26,220 --> 00:13:30,080
♪

285
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:32,260
Hi-ho, ya mangy sea dogs,
everybody drink up.

286
00:13:32,260 --> 00:13:34,280
Let's have a toast
to our new leader.

287
00:13:34,280 --> 00:13:36,270
To our new boss, Ginjo!

288
00:13:36,270 --> 00:13:38,240
(cheering)

289
00:13:38,240 --> 00:13:43,060
♪

290
00:13:43,060 --> 00:13:45,010
Congratulations to you.

291
00:13:45,010 --> 00:13:47,150
♪

292
00:13:47,150 --> 00:13:49,110
Opium, guns, and ammunition.

293
00:13:49,110 --> 00:13:50,290
With that kind of contraband,

294
00:13:50,290 --> 00:13:53,000
we'll be the kings
of the sea in no time!

295
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:54,170
But there's still
just one little thing

296
00:13:54,170 --> 00:13:56,200
that's missing from
this party if you ask me.

297
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,280
Yeah, what's that?

298
00:13:57,280 --> 00:13:59,100
Miss Shura.

299
00:13:59,100 --> 00:14:01,150
You see that big
fire over there?

300
00:14:01,150 --> 00:14:04,010
Wouldn't it be great to
burn her alive in that?

301
00:14:04,010 --> 00:14:05,010
(laughing)

302
00:14:05,010 --> 00:14:07,170
Yeah, toasted Shura.

303
00:14:07,170 --> 00:14:10,200
I would like very much to
make her suffer some more.

304
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:12,220
Too bad she died so soon.

305
00:14:12,220 --> 00:14:14,200
(laughing)

306
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:16,000
Who's that?

307
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,140
Huh?

308
00:14:17,140 --> 00:14:19,280
(grumbling)

309
00:14:19,280 --> 00:14:21,140
-Huh?
-It's Shura.

310
00:14:21,140 --> 00:14:23,120
What's Shura doing here?

311
00:14:23,120 --> 00:14:24,180
It's Shura!

312
00:14:24,180 --> 00:14:25,260
So she's alive!

313
00:14:25,260 --> 00:14:27,220
Hold it there!

314
00:14:27,220 --> 00:14:31,110
Out of my way, I have
business with Ginjo!

315
00:14:31,110 --> 00:14:34,150
You broke our code
by selling drugs.

316
00:14:34,150 --> 00:14:36,180
You have no honor,
you have no ethics,

317
00:14:36,180 --> 00:14:39,070
you are a rotten dog
to the core, Ginjo.

318
00:14:39,070 --> 00:14:41,090
I am going to finish this now.

319
00:14:41,090 --> 00:14:44,090
I will put an end to
the Sea Dragons forever.

320
00:14:44,090 --> 00:14:46,020
This will be my last duty.

321
00:14:46,020 --> 00:14:47,070
She can't do that.

322
00:14:47,070 --> 00:14:49,000
Big mistake.

323
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:52,070
Huh, so you think
you can kill me.

324
00:14:52,070 --> 00:14:53,260
You have good timing.

325
00:14:53,260 --> 00:14:55,160
As a matter of fact,
I was just saying

326
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:57,220
how I'd like to throw you
on the fire over there.

327
00:14:57,220 --> 00:14:59,110
You think you can take me?

328
00:14:59,110 --> 00:15:01,210
Well, go ahead and give
it your best shot, babe.

329
00:15:01,210 --> 00:15:03,030
Let's go!

330
00:15:03,030 --> 00:15:04,240
(grunting)

331
00:15:04,240 --> 00:15:06,230
(whirling)

332
00:15:06,230 --> 00:15:08,020
♪

333
00:15:08,020 --> 00:15:09,290
I wonder, if I beat him,

334
00:15:09,290 --> 00:15:11,180
will the others follow me?

335
00:15:11,180 --> 00:15:14,100
I'll pay you back for
doing this to my eye.

336
00:15:14,100 --> 00:15:16,100
So long!

337
00:15:16,100 --> 00:15:17,290
Yah!

338
00:15:17,290 --> 00:15:25,220
♪

339
00:15:25,220 --> 00:15:26,260
And she's tough.

340
00:15:26,260 --> 00:15:28,020
That's it!

341
00:15:28,020 --> 00:15:29,110
You're dead!

342
00:15:29,110 --> 00:15:31,160
♪

343
00:15:31,160 --> 00:15:33,070
(gasps)

344
00:15:33,070 --> 00:15:35,150
(shouting)

345
00:15:35,150 --> 00:15:38,160
What the?

346
00:15:38,160 --> 00:15:41,240
(shouting)

347
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:43,080
(gasps)

348
00:15:43,080 --> 00:15:46,080
(groaning)

349
00:15:47,290 --> 00:15:49,240
Wait a minute,
Shura, don't kill me.

350
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:51,060
You won, all right?

351
00:15:51,060 --> 00:15:54,270
I promise I won't bother
you anymore, okay?

352
00:15:54,270 --> 00:15:56,160
Is it a deal?

353
00:15:58,260 --> 00:16:00,230
(screaming)

354
00:16:02,180 --> 00:16:03,290
(laughing)

355
00:16:03,290 --> 00:16:04,270
Good job!

356
00:16:04,270 --> 00:16:06,170
I knew he wouldn't let her win.

357
00:16:06,170 --> 00:16:08,070
(groaning)

358
00:16:08,070 --> 00:16:09,050
You cheat!

359
00:16:09,050 --> 00:16:10,290
I'm a pirate,
what did you expect?

360
00:16:10,290 --> 00:16:12,230
It's not important
how you play the game,

361
00:16:12,230 --> 00:16:14,290
just to win at any cost.

362
00:16:14,290 --> 00:16:18,000
It appears that I won,
and you'll burn now.

363
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:20,000
Guess again, dirt bag.

364
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:21,090
Huh?

365
00:16:21,090 --> 00:16:25,040
♪

366
00:16:25,040 --> 00:16:26,180
What are you doing?

367
00:16:26,180 --> 00:16:27,270
He's alive, too.

368
00:16:27,270 --> 00:16:29,080
That's impossible.

369
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:31,150
Ginjo, I had to come back here

370
00:16:31,150 --> 00:16:34,110
to make sure I'd take care
of you once and for all.

371
00:16:34,110 --> 00:16:36,110
(grumbling)

372
00:16:36,110 --> 00:16:38,000
I'm warning you.

373
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:40,270
I'll fight every one
of you if I have to.

374
00:16:40,270 --> 00:16:43,010
-No!
-Tear him apart!

375
00:16:43,010 --> 00:16:45,180
(screaming)

376
00:16:45,180 --> 00:16:53,000
♪

377
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:55,120
(groaning)

378
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:57,160
(gasping and trembling)

379
00:16:57,160 --> 00:16:59,050
♪

380
00:16:59,050 --> 00:17:01,080
-Kenshin!
-Oh yeah?

381
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:02,200
Give it!

382
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:05,050
I'll take care of you!

383
00:17:05,050 --> 00:17:09,140
(screaming)

384
00:17:09,140 --> 00:17:11,110
Hey, stand still!

385
00:17:11,110 --> 00:17:12,160
What the?

386
00:17:12,160 --> 00:17:16,020
Hiten Mitsurugi style
Dragon Hammer Flash!

387
00:17:16,020 --> 00:17:19,020
(screaming)

388
00:17:19,020 --> 00:17:29,040
♪

389
00:17:29,040 --> 00:17:31,210
(gasping)

390
00:17:31,210 --> 00:17:33,070
Damn it.

391
00:17:33,070 --> 00:17:35,130
Kenshin.

392
00:17:35,130 --> 00:17:36,290
Shura, take it easy now.

393
00:17:36,290 --> 00:17:38,000
Are you okay?

394
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:39,240
That dirty rat.

395
00:17:39,240 --> 00:17:41,120
I'm gonna blow that bastard

396
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:43,280
into a billion pieces
for killing Ginjo.

397
00:17:43,280 --> 00:17:46,290
No, don't do it, there are
explosives all around here!

398
00:17:46,290 --> 00:17:48,250
You could start
a chain reaction.

399
00:17:48,250 --> 00:17:51,030
Quiet!

400
00:17:51,030 --> 00:17:53,060
(whimpering)

401
00:17:58,030 --> 00:17:59,180
(explosion)

402
00:17:59,180 --> 00:18:00,160
(gasps)

403
00:18:00,160 --> 00:18:01,230
Hey, what was that?

404
00:18:01,230 --> 00:18:02,280
What the?

405
00:18:02,280 --> 00:18:06,130
(screaming)

406
00:18:11,190 --> 00:18:13,230
(gasps)

407
00:18:13,230 --> 00:18:16,120
This is awful!

408
00:18:16,120 --> 00:18:18,240
We've got to go there
and see if Kenshin's alive.

409
00:18:18,240 --> 00:18:20,070
-Hold on!
-Let go!

410
00:18:20,070 --> 00:18:22,130
-Hey, look!
-What is it?

411
00:18:22,130 --> 00:18:23,250
Huh?

412
00:18:23,250 --> 00:18:25,090
♪

413
00:18:25,090 --> 00:18:26,290
It's Kenshin!

414
00:18:26,290 --> 00:18:29,020
Ah!

415
00:18:29,020 --> 00:18:31,090
-Kenshin!
-Kori!

416
00:18:31,090 --> 00:18:32,180
You're alive.

417
00:18:32,180 --> 00:18:33,260
Are you okay?

418
00:18:33,260 --> 00:18:37,080
I'm fine,
but Shura's really hurt.

419
00:18:37,080 --> 00:18:39,000
(explosion)

420
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:40,170
Shura, hang in there.

421
00:18:40,170 --> 00:18:43,190
You saved our lives,
and it's our turn to help you.

422
00:18:43,190 --> 00:18:46,020
I'm glad to see you, I thought
something awful happened.

423
00:18:46,020 --> 00:18:47,100
It's good to see you.

424
00:18:47,100 --> 00:18:48,250
Come on, there's
no time to lose.

425
00:18:48,250 --> 00:18:50,240
We've got to get
out of this place.

426
00:18:50,240 --> 00:18:53,090
Yeah, the whole
island's about to blow!

427
00:18:53,090 --> 00:18:56,090
♪

428
00:18:56,090 --> 00:18:58,210
(moaning)

429
00:18:58,210 --> 00:19:11,030
♪

430
00:19:11,030 --> 00:19:12,240
It's burning out of control now.

431
00:19:12,240 --> 00:19:16,220
I'm afraid it'll keep on going
until there's nothing left.

432
00:19:16,220 --> 00:19:20,060
Yeah, I guess that's the
end of Sea Dragon Island.

433
00:19:27,020 --> 00:19:28,040
♪

434
00:19:28,040 --> 00:19:29,110
Huh?

435
00:19:29,110 --> 00:19:38,000
♪

436
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:39,180
I don't know how to thank you.

437
00:19:39,180 --> 00:19:42,050
You saved my life many times.

438
00:19:42,050 --> 00:19:45,020
Don't worry about it,
you saved our lives, too.

439
00:19:45,020 --> 00:19:47,210
So, what do you think
you'll be doing now?

440
00:19:47,210 --> 00:19:49,010
I don't know.

441
00:19:49,010 --> 00:19:51,170
So much has happened
in such a short time.

442
00:19:51,170 --> 00:19:53,130
I understand.

443
00:19:53,130 --> 00:19:55,240
You must feel kinda like
you've lost everything.

444
00:19:55,240 --> 00:19:56,290
Actually, I really do--

445
00:19:56,290 --> 00:19:58,080
Wow, that's huge!

446
00:19:58,080 --> 00:19:59,090
Huh?

447
00:19:59,090 --> 00:20:01,020
I've never seen one
up close before.

448
00:20:01,020 --> 00:20:02,280
Man, these lobsters
are humongous!

449
00:20:02,280 --> 00:20:03,290
Look out!

450
00:20:03,290 --> 00:20:05,280
The only thing that
really matters in this world

451
00:20:05,280 --> 00:20:08,080
is having friends
and family nearby.

452
00:20:08,080 --> 00:20:09,230
I'm going to do it.

453
00:20:09,230 --> 00:20:12,120
I'm going to make my
father's dream come true.

454
00:20:12,120 --> 00:20:14,220
I'm going to live
an honest life.

455
00:20:14,220 --> 00:20:17,080
I'm not going to steal
from anyone again,

456
00:20:17,080 --> 00:20:19,170
and I'm going to live
at peace with the sea.

457
00:20:19,170 --> 00:20:23,070
I believe in you, Shura,
I know you can do it.

458
00:20:23,070 --> 00:20:25,120
Hey, Shura, I just
had a great idea.

459
00:20:25,120 --> 00:20:27,290
You could come live with
us at the Kamiya dojo.

460
00:20:27,290 --> 00:20:29,140
I can't do that,

461
00:20:29,140 --> 00:20:31,210
because we're wanted
by the police everywhere.

462
00:20:31,210 --> 00:20:33,150
Oh.

463
00:20:33,150 --> 00:20:35,060
But thank you.

464
00:20:35,060 --> 00:20:38,020
Kenshin, you're a rich man,
you have wonderful friends,

465
00:20:38,020 --> 00:20:39,210
but then so do I.

466
00:20:39,210 --> 00:20:41,070
-Iwazo.
-Yes.

467
00:20:41,070 --> 00:20:42,100
We have to shove off.

468
00:20:42,100 --> 00:20:43,270
-Huh?
-All right.

469
00:20:43,270 --> 00:20:47,150
We have to leave now and I'm
not really good at goodbyes.

470
00:20:47,150 --> 00:20:48,240
Hm.

471
00:20:48,240 --> 00:20:50,150
You once said to me

472
00:20:50,150 --> 00:20:53,230
that you would've liked it
if we had met as friends.

473
00:20:53,230 --> 00:20:55,040
Me, too.

474
00:20:55,040 --> 00:20:56,130
Let's do it.

475
00:20:56,130 --> 00:20:58,120
Meet again.

476
00:20:58,120 --> 00:21:00,050
As friends.

477
00:21:00,050 --> 00:21:01,190
Yeah.

478
00:21:01,190 --> 00:21:05,070
♪

479
00:21:05,070 --> 00:21:08,090
(whistle blowing)

480
00:21:08,090 --> 00:21:09,230
-Bye.
-Goodbye!

481
00:21:09,230 --> 00:21:11,100
-So long!
-And thank you.

482
00:21:11,100 --> 00:21:13,050
See you again someday!

483
00:21:13,050 --> 00:21:14,280
Take care of yourself!

484
00:21:14,280 --> 00:21:16,050
(laughing)

485
00:21:16,050 --> 00:21:17,270
Thanks for everything!

486
00:21:17,270 --> 00:21:33,897
♪

487
00:21:37,010 --> 00:21:39,150
♪

488
00:21:39,150 --> 00:21:42,210
(singing in foreign language)

489
00:21:42,210 --> 00:23:08,250
♪

